꾆 4. Create Project Using Git Bash
Open Git Bash
mkdir AI-CI-Project
cd AI-CI-Project
touch app.py test_app.py requirements.txt Jenkinsfile
꾆 5. Add Code (using Notepad)
Open files on git bash
notepad app.py
Paste:
def add(a,b):
 return a+b
notepad test_app.py
Paste:
import unittest
from app import add
class TestAdd(unittest.TestCase):
 def test_add(self):
 self.assertEqual(add(2,3),5)
if __name__ == "__main__":
 unittest.main()
notepad requirements.txt
Paste:
pytest
notepad Jenkinsfile
Paste:
pipeline {
 agent any
 stages {
 stage('Install Dependencies') {
 steps {
 bat 'pip3 install -r requirements.txt'
 }
 }
 stage('Run Tests') {
 steps {
 bat 'python -m unittest'
 }
 }
 }
}
